        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33909",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This would not work.\n\nYour change would force objects to be run through the foreach loop which causes a warning as objects are casted to string. And the API of getEscaped() declares that the input value has to be a string and not a object.\n\nUsing this I would simply define a own Default Filter which accepts and returns objects.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-25T14:51:21.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-25T14:51:21.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33910",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Additionally I would not know how escaping of a object should work.\nEscaping can only be applied to a string. Therefor a casting is expected behaviour.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-25T15:13:36.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-25T15:13:36.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33968",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Closing this issue as Won't Fix after a short discussion with the dev-team.\n\nReason:\ngetEscaped() escapes data which is intended for usage within the View. This method does not handle non native types. What should be escaped within an object? It would be casted to an string in any case.\n\nTherefor there is no solution for the described case. You would have to extend the needed classes to provide the methodology you wish.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-26T11:47:33.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-26T11:47:33.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
